The Yobe State Commissioner Ministry of Basic and Secondary Education, Dr. Muhammad Sani Idris said they have concluded arrangements to conduct extra Lessons for senior school students who are writing 2020 WEAC and NECO on Yobe Broadcasting Corporation (YBC), Facebook Streaming and whatsapp platforms. Schools in Yobe state were closed down following the report of a corona virus pandemic in Nigeria with a view to avoid the spread of the disease among students, teachers among other academic and non-academic staff across the state. A statement issued by the Permanent Secretary of the ministry Alhaji Yakubu Dokshi said the extra lessons will be on English Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry. Similarly subjects such as Biology, Information and Communication Technology (ICT), Economics and Government will also conduction during the extra lesson. The statement said, “Parents and guardians are therefore advised to ensure that their wards take advantage of the initiative by listening to the programme which will be aired on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays, Saturdays and Sundays with the overall objective of recording excellent results.” The ministry has already fixed Tuesday 7th April, 2020 for the commencement of the lesson where some teachers trained for the extra lesson will be solving question papers of WEAC of the past ten years.